title: World’s first self-stabilising walking exoskeleton enters stroke rehab tria
excerpt: Wandercraft's pioneering exoskeleton, the Atlante X, has entered a rehabilitation trial in Germany.

title: Pitt and CMU To Create Autonomous Robotic Trauma Care System
excerpt: CMU and the University of Pittsburgh School of Medicine have received funding from the U.S. Department of Defense to create an autonomous trauma care system that fits in a backpack — or, as shown here, a folded stretcher.
